# Units
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------

oakcurric:unit-3409
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Accurate and precise cooking"@en ;
  curric:slug "accurate-and-precise-cooking" ;
  rdfs:comment """Through three recipes, the emphasis of this unit is on accurate and precise use of
  a range of food skills, and independent working. High standards of food safety are
  embedded, and pupils modify recipes for health and explore food science in action and the
  cost of ingredients."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Cooking independently provides pupils with the confidence and transferable
  skills to cook at home and apply their learning life long. Accuracy and precision are
  refined, based on previous work in Years 7 and 8 of becoming more proficient in a range of
  food skills, and employing strategies to keep safe and hygienic. Pupils continue to secure
  and fine-tune their food skills in Year 9, preparing, cooking and presenting a range of
  dishes, while embedding food safety and hygiene, and deepening the application of food
  science.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3409-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3409-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3409-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3409-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3409-5 ;
  curric:id "3409"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.900557Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-food-and-nutrition-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-food-origins-and-provenance ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-science-of-food ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-preparation-and-cooking ,
    oakcurric:thread-healthy-eating-and-nutrition ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-hygiene-and-safety ,
    oakcurric:thread-sensory-evaluation .

oakcurric:unit-3411
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Global food challenges"@en ;
  curric:slug "global-food-challenges" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit investigates the pressure on food systems, caused by climate change and
  a growing population. Pupils critique these challenges and explore principles of more
  sustainable diets, balancing the needs of the planet and human health. Practical work
  reinforces these principles in action."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Climate change and a growing population present real challenges to our
  global food systems. Examining these challenges enables us to be better informed about the
  decisions we make as consumers. The application of previous learning in Year 8, around
  strategies to create healthier and more sustainable diets, and consider the needs of people,
  are built upon and expanded. This learning provides pupils with a firm foundation to be
  better informed consumers, making good decisions based on their needs and beliefs.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3411-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3411-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3411-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3411-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3411-5 ;
  curric:id "3411"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.902558Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-food-and-nutrition-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-sustainability-and-climate-change ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-origins-and-provenance ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-science-of-food ,
    oakcurric:thread-consumer-awareness ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-preparation-and-cooking ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-hygiene-and-safety ,
    oakcurric:thread-sensory-evaluation .

oakcurric:unit-3404
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Informed food choices"@en ;
  curric:slug "informed-food-choices" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit develops pupils' knowledge of food choice, and how occasion and location
  can have an influence. Food skills and nutrition understanding are further developed
  through practical work, and the use of components are explored."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Throughout life, a variety of factors affect the food and drink we choose,
  some of which are personal preferences, while others are cultural, linked to occasion, and
  where we are and who we are with. Building on previous work around Food culture and Consumer
  awareness in Year 6, pupils critique choices and suggest alternatives. Looking forward to
  Year 8, pupils address the influence of ingredient availability, cuisine, cooking technique,
  and equipment on food choice locally and around the world.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3404-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3404-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3404-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3404-4 ;
  curric:id "3404"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.025830Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-food-and-nutrition-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-science-of-food ,
    oakcurric:thread-consumer-awareness ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-culture ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-preparation-and-cooking ,
    oakcurric:thread-healthy-eating-and-nutrition ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-hygiene-and-safety ,
    oakcurric:thread-sensory-evaluation .

oakcurric:unit-3407
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "More sustainable diets"@en ;
  curric:slug "more-sustainable-diets" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils identify ways in which a diet can be healthier and more
  sustainable. Pupils suggest practical ways in which a range of strategies could be
  implemented. Through cooking two dishes, pupils apply this learning, giving them tools to
  adapt recipes in the future."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """There are a number of strategies that can be employed to create healthier,
  more sustainable diets. Practical strategies allow consumers to make a difference to their
  health and the planet, such as including more fruit and vegetables, and having a greater
  diversity of protein sources. This builds on the threads Food origins and provenance, and
  Sustainability. In Year 9, pupils investigate global food challenges, further exploring the
  principles of how diets can be more sustainable.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3407-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3407-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3407-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3407-4 ;
  curric:id "3407"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.216476Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-food-and-nutrition-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-sustainability-and-climate-change ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-origins-and-provenance ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-science-of-food ,
    oakcurric:thread-consumer-awareness ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-preparation-and-cooking ,
    oakcurric:thread-healthy-eating-and-nutrition ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-hygiene-and-safety .

oakcurric:unit-3410
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Health and dietary needs"@en ;
  curric:slug "health-and-dietary-needs" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils explore key nutritional needs throughout life, and allergies,
  food labelling, portion size and health conditions. They plan dishes and menus, and
  describe how diets can be changed for health to meet the needs of different groups of
  people."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Dietary and nutritional needs change throughout life, and being able to
  plan diets for the needs of different people is important to minimise any potential
  consequences of poor diet. This builds on work in Year 8 around the name, source and function
  of different nutrients, and the application of healthy eating guidelines. Going forward,
  pupils will have the knowledge, skills and strategies to plan diets and make meals for
  themselves and others, now and in the future.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3410-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3410-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3410-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3410-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3410-5 ;
  curric:id "3410"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.277402Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-food-and-nutrition-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-science-of-food ,
    oakcurric:thread-consumer-awareness ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-preparation-and-cooking ,
    oakcurric:thread-healthy-eating-and-nutrition ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-hygiene-and-safety .

oakcurric:unit-3405
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Cooking techniques and proficiency"@en ;
  curric:slug "cooking-techniques-and-proficiency" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit extends pupils' cooking techniques, focusing on their food skill
  proficiency. Pupils develop food skills and apply their nutrition understanding. Recipe
  modification is undertaken, through nutritional analysis, and the functional properties of
  key ingredients are analysed."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Being proficient with a range of food skills enables us to prepare and
  cook more complex recipes, extending our repertoire. This confidence also enables us to
  successfully modify recipes for health, variety and preference. Progressing from Year 7,
  through the thread of Food preparation and cooking, pupils continue to refine their food
  skills, embedding The science of food, and Sensory evaluation learning, leading to more
  independent work. In Year 9 the focus is on greater precision and accuracy in preparation and
  cooking, and the exploration of food science in practice.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3405-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3405-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3405-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3405-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3405-5 ;
  curric:id "3405"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.475101Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-food-and-nutrition-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-science-of-food ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-origins-and-provenance ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-preparation-and-cooking ,
    oakcurric:thread-healthy-eating-and-nutrition ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-hygiene-and-safety .

oakcurric:unit-3403
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Food origins"@en ;
  curric:slug "food-origins" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils describe the origins of different foods, identifying how they have been
  produced, processed and sold. Food labels are used to investigate ingredient origins.
  Pupils cook two dishes, investigating ingredient source, as well as functional properties."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Understanding the origin of ingredients allows informed decisions to be
  made, such as location, farming practice or ethics. Food labels and other information
  indicates origins. This builds on from previous work in Year 5 around Food origins and
  provenance, and safe and edible food in Year 6. In Year 8, pupils investigate Sustainability
  and further their learning around Consumer awareness factors, such as food choice, suggesting
  practical strategies that could be implemented for healthier and more sustainable diets.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3403-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3403-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3403-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3403-4 ;
  curric:id "3403"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.582695Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-food-and-nutrition-key-stage-3 ;
