    oakcurric:thread-healthy-eating-and-nutrition ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-hygiene-and-safety ,
    oakcurric:thread-sensory-evaluation .

oakcurric:unit-3401
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Independent and confident cooking"@en ;
  curric:slug "independent-and-confident-cooking" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit introduces pupils to working in a different environment, learning new
  skills and procedures, and using a range of equipment. The focus is on establishing
  hygiene and safety procedures, and the food skills measuring, peeling, cutting and using
  the hob. Sensory work is undertaken."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Learning how to prepare and cook food safely in unfamiliar environments
  builds confidence, engagement and adherence to procedures for health. Transitioning from Year
  6, pupils' prior food experiences progress in terms of food skill accuracy, and range of
  ingredients and equipment used, via the threads of Food preparation and cooking, Food hygiene
  and safety, and Sensory evaluation. This lays the foundation for more complex and independent
  cooking, and investigating The science of food during Year 7. In Year 8, Food preparation and
  cooking progresses, with a focus on technique and proficiency.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3401-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3401-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3401-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3401-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3401-5 ;
  curric:id "3401"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.281532Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-food-and-nutrition-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-food-preparation-and-cooking ,
    oakcurric:thread-healthy-eating-and-nutrition ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-hygiene-and-safety ,
    oakcurric:thread-sensory-evaluation .

oakcurric:unit-3408
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Local food to worldwide cuisine"@en ;
  curric:slug "local-food-to-worldwide-cuisine" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit focuses on the wide range of cuisines, ingredients, cooking techniques
  and equipment that are used around the world. Pupils explore food imports, food produced
  in the UK, and food waste. They cook two dishes to highlight cuisine differences,
  undertaking different types of evaluation."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Cuisines are a set of cooking traditions and techniques, associated with a
  specific culture, region and ingredients. This recognition provides insight into cooking and
  recipe choice, fulfilling consumer tastes for more international cuisines, while honouring
  traditional UK dishes. This work builds on previous learning in Year 7 around the threads of
  Food culture, Consumer awareness, and Food origins and provenance. During Year 9, pupils
  further reflect on food culture, and how food forms part of our identity, heritage,
  tradition, custom and celebration.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3408-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3408-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3408-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3408-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3408-5 ;
  curric:id "3408"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.296405Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
