    oakcurric:thread-food-preparation-and-cooking ,
    oakcurric:thread-food-hygiene-and-safety ,
    oakcurric:thread-sensory-evaluation .

oakcurric:unit-3406
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Energy and nutrients: source and function"@en ;
  curric:slug "energy-and-nutrients-source-and-function" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils describe the source and function of macro and micro nutrients, as well as
  fibre and water in the diet for health. The concept of energy balance is reviewed, and
  pupils undertake nutritional analysis of recipes."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Energy, nutrients, fibre and water are needed in different amounts, are
  from a range of sources, and have specific functions for health. This builds on previous
  Eatwell Guide learning, food groups and proportions in Year 8, enabling pupils to apply
  nutritional knowledge when making healthier choices and modifying recipes, through linking
  food source and function. In Year 9, pupils explore changing nutritional needs throughout
  life, as well as allergies and health conditions.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3406-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3406-2 ,
